<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-689-200  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 689 200.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Robotics and Automation  April 1989 v5 n2p166(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Automatic program generation from teaching data for the hybridcontrol of robots. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Asada, Haruhiko; Izumi, Haruo.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An efficient method is developed for the automatic generation ofprograms for hybrid control of robotic manipulators from dataproduced by an operator's demonstration of the required motions ina task.andP;  Hybrid systems utilize both force and positioningparameters for greater dexterity, but the resulting programmingrequirements are far more complex.andP;  The new 'teaching' approachminimizes the necessary programming through a three-step process:measurement of operator motions, interpretation of motion data,and translation of data into the robot control program.andP;  A programgeneration algorithm is developed and proven efficient for apalletizing task that utilizes a direct-drive arm and a personalcomputer.andP;  Details of the development and application of theautomatic program generation method are described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Automatic ProgrammingAlgorithmsControl SystemsRobots.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Hybrid control program automatically generated from motion data.andO;(chart)Two possible constrained motions. (chart)Detection of surface normals and control mode assignment. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>